{"type":"message","id":"d5093d2e","parentId":"045734ba","timestamp":"2026-03-02T05:43:24.950Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Done. Updated SOUL.md with a clean, personality-focused definition. Let Gerson know it's set.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Done. `SOUL.md` updated.\n\nQubit is now defined as:\n- **Calm strategist** — intentional, not reactive\n- **Timing-aware** — speaks when it matters, not just because\n- **Adaptive verbosity** — matches depth to domain\n- **Strategic insight** — sees around corners\n- **Quiet by default** — no nagging unless urgent\n\nAnything else to configure before we get started?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":318,"output":112,"cacheRead":14528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14958,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772430197565}}
{"type":"message","id":"bee60209","parentId":"d5093d2e","timestamp":"2026-03-02T05:43:30.220Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-02 05:43 UTC] Timezone Doctrine (Critical) Prompt 3 — Add Timezone Rules to TOOLS.md Update TOOLS.md with strict timezone doctrine: System time = UTC User-facing time = Asia/Kolkata Due checks must use UTC only User-visible timestamps must use Asia/Kolkata All scheduled items must store both UTC and IST timestamps Keep it short and rule-based."}],"timestamp":1772430210215}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f1f1791","parentId":"bee60209","timestamp":"2026-03-02T05:43:37.677Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to update TOOLS.md with timezone rules. Let me read the current TOOLS.md first, then append the timezone doctrine.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ee54825e79bc443295636a66","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":448,"output":49,"cacheRead":14528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15025,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772430210219}}
{"type":"message","id":"039dbd4d","parentId":"4f1f1791","timestamp":"2026-03-02T05:43:37.684Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ee54825e79bc443295636a66","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772430217682}}
{"type":"message","id":"60189ae2","parentId":"039dbd4d","timestamp":"2026-03-02T05:43:52.703Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll update TOOLS.md with the timezone doctrine, keeping the existing content but adding the timezone rules at the top since they're critical operational rules.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e5402e211ce647b288e2e6ad","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md","content":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## Timezone Doctrine\n\n- **System time** = UTC (internal operations, due checks, scheduling logic)\n- **User-facing time** = Asia/Kolkata (timestamps shown to Gerson)\n- **Due checks** = UTC only (never compare against local time)\n- **User-visible timestamps** = Always Asia/Kolkata (format: `[Day YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM IST]`)\n- **Scheduled items** = Store both UTC and IST timestamps\n\n---\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":322,"output":354,"cacheRead":14912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15588,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772430217684}}
