{"type":"message","id":"b744b370","parentId":"a771ada8","timestamp":"2026-03-02T05:51:11.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to update policy.md with rules about manual.md behavior. There's a bit of a contradiction here - in the domain template, I put manual.md at the root level, but now they're saying it lives under system-artifacts. Let me re-read the request.\n\nThey want:\n- manual.md represents current mode of operation\n- It lives under system-artifacts\n- It is updated during quiet hours\n- It reflects active operating strategy\n- It does NOT label itself as an experiment\n- Experiments modify manual.md silently\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Update policy.md with these rules\n2. Possibly move the template's manual.md to system-artifacts/ to match this rule\n\nLet me update policy.md and also fix the template structure.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_eb1d8889bff74b20955bd8db","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/system/policy.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1314,"output":175,"cacheRead":18624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20113,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772430660882}}
{"type":"message","id":"1d440d44","parentId":"b744b370","timestamp":"2026-03-02T05:51:11.592Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_eb1d8889bff74b20955bd8db","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# System Policy\n\nOperational rules for Qubit. Structured and concise.\n\n## Loops\n\n| Loop | Interval | Action |\n|------|----------|--------|\n| Heartbeat | ~30s | Send due messages only |\n| Orchestrator | ~15m | Select one domain, perform one best action |\n\n## Quiet Hours\n\n- **Window:** 00:00–05:00 IST\n- **Rules:**\n  - No outbound messages\n  - Never modify `user-artifacts/`\n  - Internal processing only (learning, experiments)\n\n## Phases\n\n| Phase | Focus |\n|-------|-------|\n| Phase 1 | Experimentation + learning |\n| Phase 2 | Prepare daily briefs (after system matures) |\n\n## Daily Briefs\n\n- **Time:** 05:00 IST (end of quiet hours)\n- **Format:** One ultra-concise brief per domain\n- **Delivery:** Single consolidated message\n\n## Urgency Rule\n\nAn item is **urgent** if:\n1. Explicitly marked `urgent`, OR\n2. Due same day\n\n**Only urgent items** allow persistent reminders. Non-urgent items surface once, then wait.\n\n## User-Artifacts Rule\n\n- `user-artifacts/` = user-owned files\n- **Never modify** during quiet hours\n- Read freely anytime\n- Write only outside quiet hours, with intent\n\n## Queue Awareness\n\nBefore orchestrator proposes any action for a domain:\n1. Read upcoming queued messages for that channel\n2. Avoid redundant or nagging proposals\n3. Skip if queue already covers the intent\n\n## Domain Structure\n\n```\nsystem/domains/<channel_id>/\n├── purpose.md        # Read every planning cycle\n├── activity.log      # Action history\n├── manual.md         # User-defined domain rules\n├── user-artifacts/   # User-owned files\n├── system-artifacts/ # Qubit-managed files\n└── artifacts/        # Shared assets\n```\n\n## Purpose.md Rule\n\n- **Read:** Every planning cycle (orchestrator tick)\n- **Focus:** Heavy when empty (learn domain actively)\n- **Update:** Rarely, only when purpose shifts\n- **Editable:** Active hours only (05:00–00:00 IST)\n\n---\n\nThis policy governs all system behavior. Refer to `timezone.md` for time handling.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772430671590}}
